    "description": "Black garlic sounds scary, but it's just a type of caramelised garlic, made by heating whole bulbs very slowly over the course of several weeks. The result is a soft, squidgy clove that has a sweet, balsamic flavour. Perfect for adding instant umami to a burger! We've served ours with charred lettuce and a black mayo. Welcome to the dark side!",
